Hungarian Forint Strengthens After Biggest Fall in Seven Months

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-07-19T06:25:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/hungarian-forint-strengthens-after-biggest-fall-in-seven-months.html
The forint strengthened for the
first time in four days after posting the biggest one-day fall
in seven months yesterday.  The Hungarian currency gained 0.3 percent to 272.6 per euro
as of 8:20 a.m. in Budapest after depreciating 1.3 percent
yesterday, the most on a closing basis since Dec. 20.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest 
 agergely@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
